## Description
The **Manage invoices (EI) **task allows to receive invoices from a Batch Workflow and prepare them for processing by the Electronic Invoicing and Legal Electronic Archiving components of the Doxee Platform. It validates incoming invoices and generates the metadata that is necessary for sending the invoices to SDI and the Documents and Analytics Portals.

## Principles of operation
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

The Manage invoices (EI) task represents the entry-point for other Batch Workflows tasks, for example for interacting with the Legal Electronic Archiving or Electronic Invoicing services. A simplified example of the processing possibilities of the output branches of the task can be seen below:

## 
## Configuration
![](data:image/png;base64,)

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- In the **Profile **field, enter the profile ID to use.

> Important

The profile must be configured for Electronic Invoicing.

- Connect the task to another task in the workflow and select a Branch type:

> Note

The configuration of the connector determines the output of the Manage invoices (EI) task (see **Output** below).

**Default**

- **Documents Portal**

- **Discard**

## Input
- The expected input of the Manage invoices (EI) task is the following:

- **Electronic invoice(s) **(XML format)

- **Manifest file **for each electronic invoice containing all metadata (XML format)

> Note

The name of the XML manifest must be *manifest.xml *(case-sensitive).

- *(optional) ***400/410 files **for Tracking and Reporting (*.400h, .410h, .400d, .410d*, case insensitive)

- *(optional) ***eipa.delay file **for delaying the sending of the EI package to SdI

### Example manifest file
The *manifest.xml *file must contain the following tags:

- **&lt;EI&gt; **root tag

**&lt;MANIFEST&gt; **tag(s) (one for each invoice)

**&lt;INVOICES&gt; **tag

**&lt;INVOICE&gt; **tag containing all metadata of the invoice

## Output
The output of the Manage invoices (EI) task depends on the configuration of the connector to the next task in the workflow, and may be one or more of the following:

- **Default branch **(Branch type: *Default*): Contains the files needed to create FI packages for SdI and to archive invoices in the Legal Electronic Archiving service

- **Ei Documents branch **(Branch type: *Documents Portal*): Contains the files needed to load the invoices to the Documents Portal

- **Discard branch **(Branch type: *Discard*): Contains the invoices which did not pass the internal invoice validator check

For further processing of the output branches of the Manage invoices (EI) task, see the respective sections below.

### Default branch
The default output branch contains the files needed to create FI packages for SdI and to archive invoices in the Legal Electronic Archiving service.

> Note

This branch will only be created if the input contains at least one valid invoice.

The output consists of the following items:

- **Electronic invoice(s) **(XML format)

- **invoices.manifest **(JSON format)

**Example invoices.manifest.json file**

`{"invoices":[{"invoice":{"identifier":"dd7a9cd6-c35e-4cb8-83e1-f304d55f3cc2","filename":"IT72439856100_cHjhZ.  xml"}},{"invoice":{"identifier":"feeca45d-2c10-4e18-bc23-2387cb9c7f15","filename":"IT72439856100_F5hI7.xml"}}...]}`
- *(optional) ***Signed file **of each invoice

> Note

This output will only be present if Signing has been enabled in the profile configuration.

- *(optional) ***400/410 files **for Tracking and Reporting transferred from input and renamed to *ANALYTICS.400H*, *ANALYTICS.410H*, *ANALYTI CS.400D*, *ANALYTICS.410D*

> Note

This output will only be present if the input contained Tracking and Reporting files (see Input above).Note

- *(optional) ***Legal Electronic Archiving files **containing one row for each invoice (**.idx *format) . The filename has the structure **${work-unit-name-without-extension}_${lot-number}.idx **(for example *workunit_0000100139104902.idx*).

> Note

This output will only be present if archiving has been enabled in the profile configuration.

**.idx *file with the filename structure **${work-unit-name-without-extension}_${lot-number}.idx **(for example *workunit_0000100139 104902.idx*)

**Example *.idx file**

`PRODUCTDEVELOPMENT@|@IT72439856100_F5hI7.xml@|@IT72439856100_F5hI7.
xml@|@FATTV1@|@4193@|@@|@source@|@k00@|@k01@|@k02@|@k03@|@k04@|@k05@|@k06@|@k07@|@k08@|@k09@|@k10@|@k11@|@k1  2@|@k13@|@k14@|@FATTV1202400000000000065096001@|@22/02/2024@|@description@|@@|@1`
- **.tracking *file with the filename structure **${work-unit-name-without-extension}_${lot-number}.tracking **(for example *workunit_00 00100139104902.tracking*)

**Example *.tracking file**

`IDJOB=100139104989
IDPACKAGE=0000100139104902`
- *(optional) ***eipa.delay file **for delaying the sending of packages to SdI

For further processing of the default output branch of the Manage invoices (EI) task, see [Archive Documents (LEA) Batch Workflow Task Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/archive-documents-lea-batch-workflow-task-reference) and [Create Packages (EI) Batch Workflow Task Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/create-packages-ei-batch-workflow-task-reference).

### Ei Documents branch
The Ei Documents output branch contains the files needed to load the invoices to the Documents Portal.

> Note

This branch will only be created if Documents has been enabled in the profile configuration.

The output consists of the following items:

- **Electronic invoice(s) **(JSON format)

For further processing of the documents output branch of the Manage invoices (EI) task, see [Load Documents (EI) Batch Workflow Task Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/load-documents-ei-batch-workflow-task-reference).

### Discard branch
The Discard output branch contains the invoices which did not pass the internal invoice validator checks.

> Note

This branch will only be created if the input contains at least one invalid invoice.

The output consists of the following items:

- **Electronic invoice(s) **(XML format)

- ****.discard *file(s) **for each invoice with the filename structure **${invoice-file-name-without-extension}.discard **(for example *IT72439856100 _4K842.discard*)

**Example *.discard file**

`ERR_00200: File non conforme al formato con messaggio cvc-complex-type.2.4.b: The content of element 'DettaglioLinee' is not complete. One of '{AliquotaIVA}' is expected.
ERR_00200: File non conforme al formato con messaggio cvc-complex-type.2.4.a: Invalid content was found starting with element 'ImponibileImporto'. One of '{AliquotaIVA}' is expected.`
